<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>DOM Example</title>
    <script>
        function showMessage() {
            document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Welcome to  
JavaScript DOM!";
        }
    </script>
</head>
<body>

    <h2>Dynamic Content using DOM</h2>

    <button onclick="showMessage()">Click Here</button>

    <p id="demo"></p>

</body>
</html>
 
Simple code explanation
Function
function showMessage()
This function runs when the button is clicked.
DOM selection
document.getElementById("demo")
This selects the paragraph whose id is demo.
Dynamic content
innerHTML = "Welcome to JavaScript DOM!";
This changes the content of the paragraph dynamically.
Button
<button onclick="showMessage()">
When the button is clicked, the function runs.
________________________________________
Short viva explanation
If teacher says “Explain your program,” you can say:
“This program uses JavaScript DOM to change webpage content dynamically. When the button is clicked, JavaScript selects the paragraph by id and displays a message.”
