Common viva questions
1. What is DOM?
DOM stands for Document Object Model.
2. What does DOM do?
It allows JavaScript to access and change HTML elements.
3. What does getElementById() do?
It selects an HTML element using its id.
4. What is innerHTML?
It is used to change the content inside an HTML element.
5. What does onclick do?
It runs JavaScript code when the button is clicked.
